<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-55-0643 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Federal Republic of Germany holds position five on the list of theworld's biggest energy consumers. This alone is a fact that puts specialemphasis on the public discussion about the peaceful use of nuclear energy,in addition to the current events such as incidents and accidents innuclear installations. A sober review of the pros and cons of nuclearenergy for power generation has to take into account the economic effectsand the costs to be borne by the national economy as a result of immediateabandonment of nuclear energy. The article in hand discusses chances,problems, and alternatives to nuclear energy (solar energy and wind power).</TEXT></DOC>